name: Daily Grind
description: Cold conditioned on a hefty dose of ColombiaDulima Excelso from our friends at Valiant Coffee Roasters. Served on nitro for maximum creamy goodness.

name: Cold Grind
description:
Clean. Crisp. Uncompromising.

Cold Grind is a no-nonsense premium lager brewed for those who respect the grind. Crafted with precision and patience, it pours a brilliant golden hue with a frothy white head. Expect a light, bready malt backbone balanced by a subtle hop bitterness and a refreshingly dry finish. Cold-fermented and conditioned for extra smoothness, its the perfect beer for unwinding after a hard dayor gearing up for the next challenge.

name: Velvet Funeral - Barrel
description: Aged gracefully for 18 months in a combination of Blanton's and Buffalo Trace barrels.

name: Zero Degrees
description:
100% Mosaic and Mosaic Cryo hops bring you vibrant flavors and aromas of blueberry fields, mango flesh, and top shelf herb.

2024 GABF - Silver Medal - American-Style Strong Pale Ale

2023 GABF - Bronze Medal - India Pale Lager or Cold India Pale Ale

name: Shred IPA
description:
Introducing simply - Shred IPA

We carefully selected a blend of Mosaic, Citra, Simcoe, and CTZ hops to showcase intense hoppy deliciousness over a lean malt canvas. Bright tropical fruits paired with dank cannabis notes shine through on the palate for a most excellent sensory experience

name: Good Buds
description:
Pop, pour, and pass it to your left. This West Coast IPA hits with sticky pine, bright citrus, and that dank snap of bitternessloaded with Simcoe, Apollo, Amarillo & Chinook hops.

Whether youre blazing trails or just blazing, this ones for the real ones.â€¨

Pairs with your couch, your crew & a good sesh.

name: Hand Picked
description: Bursting with hand-selected Citra, Simcoe, and El Dorado hops- this beer drips with an abundance of peach nectar, rock fruit, and honeydew flesh.

name: Spent Greens
description:
Celebrate the harvest This is our annual tribute to the most exciting time of year in the world of hops.

We started with a massive dose of fresh-picked Centennial hops, rushed straight off the bines from the fine folks at Crosby Hops.

We then built upon that vibrant, green foundation with a high-stakes dry hop of Simcoe, Nelson, and Nectaron. The result is a West Coast IPA that bridges the Pacific Northwest and the Southern Hemispherea wild symphony of wet pine and lemon meringue from the fresh Centennials, layered with the dank, stone fruit of Simcoe, the diesel notes of Nelson, and the explosive tropical passion fruit of Nectaron.

name: Murk Level Midnight
description:
Hazy DIPA collaboration with our pals at Pure Project Brewing.

Prepare to get totally murked out from an abundance of Nelson, Strata, Citra, and Simcoe hops.

Tasting notes Pineapple Sorbet. Peach Rings. Fresh Herbs.

name: Macro Blaster
description:
We took our super crushable award-winning Micro Blaster and amplified it up to another level

Lock and load with Macro Blaster DIPA, the ultimate hop cannon designed to blast your senses into overdrive Like the wildest water gun fight on the block, this brew comes charging with Mosaic, Mosaic Cryo, Mosaic DynaBoost, Nelson, Nelson Cryo, Simcoe, & Simcoe Cryo.

Soaked and saturated with flavors and aromas of crushed gooseberries, resin sauce, and pineapple gelato.

name: Training Wheels
description:
Brewed with copious amounts oats and spelt, then hopped intensely with Citra Cryo, Citra, and Strata hops.

Apricot Sorbet. Dole Whip. Sativa Flowers.

name: Crypt Lord
description:
Shrouded in haze and brewed in the shadows, Crypt Lord is a Hazy IPA that rules with an eerie intensity. Bursting with spectral waves of passion fruit, kiwi, and diesel notes from the use of 100% Nelson hops - its smooth, pillowy mouthfeel conceals a sinister hop punch that lingers beyond the grave.

Low bitterness, high mystique  this is the haze that haunts.

name: Cease And Deceased
description:
Forged in the fires of oblivion and brewed with the fury of the damned, Cease and Deceased is a relentless West Coast IPA born from the unholy alliance between Shred Beer Company and the grim masters of lupulin at Ghost Town Brewing.

A riff of citrus-peel bitterness, gooseberry, and sticky resin from the onslaught of Nelson Cryo, Mosaic Cryo, Riwaka, and Cascade hops tears through your senses like a chainsaw solo at midnight. The malt backbone is razor-thin just enough to keep the chaos in check before dropping off into a clean, bone-dry finish that hits harder than a double kick to the chest.

Clear and golden as a dying sun, this West Coast IPA is sharp, loud, and merciless. No haze. No mercy. No surrender

name: Hammock Time
description: Itâ€™s summer, and that means it's Hammock Time. This Blonde Ale recalls flavors of fresh apricots, honey, and a hint of hoppiness bundled in a refreshing light ale. Perfect for those days when all you want to do is find the nearest hammock, kick off the flip flops, and chill out in the shade.

name: 1-2 Punch
description: This beer packs a hell of a punch! Of fruit that is...1-2 Punch is a hazy IPA that checks all the boxes- dynamite hops flavor from Citra, Amarillo and Mosaic, paired with Peach and Mango to punch up your palate. Crooked Lane's customer favorite!

name: Mandarin Pale Ale
style: American Pale Ale With Fresh Mandarin Juice
description: Mandarin Pale Ale features fresh-squeezed juice from Colwell Thundering Herd Mandarin Ranch. Itâ€™s crisp and satisfying with a delightful citrus aroma and dry finish. Mandarin season may only come once each year, but now you can raise a glass and celebrate year round!

name: Discover The Unicorn
description: Our love of West Coast IPA runs deep- this IPA checks all the boxes. Clear, crisp and balanced bitterness, on point with layered notes of ripe mango, melon, grapefruit and just the right amount of dank.

name: SR-16
description: SR 16 inspires with a sense of IPA adventure. A double that drinks like a single, you wonâ€™t believe the burst of Citra and Amarillo hops that resides within. One taste and youâ€™re hooked â€“ youâ€™ve been warned.

name: Women Of Iron
description: Crooked Lane and Iron Rose FC are a badass matchup! In honor of our new partnership, we crafted this West Coast IPA with a unique blend of Chinook, Cashmere, Idaho 7 and Riwaka for a big melon and spicy nose, backed up with powerful grapefruit hop character. We are bringing this IPA to our core lineup, so we can celebrate Women of Iron all year long!

name: Mic Czech
description: Brewed with the fine folks at Infusion Taproom in Lincoln, CA for their 10th Anniversary, this delicious Czech-style Pilsner is a variation of our last Czech Pils, Zephyr Ridge. With the same yummy citrus and floral Saaz hops we added an addition of Tettnang hops. Which offers aromas of herbal, woodsy spiciness

name: Camp Pendleton Pils
description: This beer is brewed in memory of Officer Cameron Landon, who was a police officer, Marine and father. It will help benefit law enforcement officers, first responders and veterans that suffer from Post Traumatic Stress (PTS). We used the Mic Czech as the base beer for this West Coast Pils, we dry hopped the hell out of this highly drinkable, extremely aromatic beer with Nelson, Nectaron, and Citra. This combination of southern hemisphere hops creates undeniably delicious aromas and flavors of mango, lychee, and pineapple.

name: Veedles Brau
description: Thereâ€™s nothing quite like a good KÃ¶lsch. Subtle fruit character, noble German hops, light malt backbone, and crisp finish make our KÃ¶lsch-style ale exquisitely refreshing. Veedels are districts within the city of KÃ¶ln, and and Veedels BrÃ¤u we transport you there for biergarten bliss.

name: Wobblor
description: German lager of the richest, most decadent character, Doppelbock was originally liquid bread, brewed to sustain the faithful while fasting. Now you can enjoy it without the hardship! Wobblorâ€™s caramel, toffee, and rich malty flavors delight the senses and fortify against evil and adversity.

name: Oktoberfest
description: We do traditional styles korrekt! Itâ€™s all German ingredients that go into this delicious amber lager, with complex malt flavor and aroma, brilliant color, and a crisp, dry finish. Time to grab your stein, your dirdnl, your lederhosen, and get your schunkeln on! Oans, zwoa, drei, gâ€™suffa!

name: Mortal Wombat
description: Choose Your Destiny . . . with our latest West Coast Double IPA, Mortal Wombat. The trio of Nelson, Nectaron and Motueka attacks your palate with a Flawless Victory!

name: Steely Dano West Coast IPA
description: Dano, one of our beloved brewers, is a BIG-HEARTED teddy bear, famous for naming many of our brewery features and experiences. To honor him and his wifeâ€™s propensity to foster stray kittens aka The Sh**ty Kitty Rescue Steely Dano was created, a west coast IPA built to Danoâ€™s strict specifications; crisp, dry and pale with Cryo BRU-1, Idaho 7, and Rakau. It puts the pine in pineapple!

name: Survivors & Heroes West Coast IPA
description: Survivors and Heroes is a classic and sturdily built west coast IPA, with a retro malt backbone and forward looking Anchovy and Elani Cryo hops, delivering a fresh pop of pine and citrus. Anchovy, a new small batch hop, delivers a one-of-a-kind flavor featuring raspberry and pine, while Elani features stone fruit and orange zest- needless to say, this flavor combo is uniquely refreshing!

name: Blood Simple Hefeweisen with Blood Orange
description: Blood Simple is the Radler reinvented... starting with a traditional German-style Hefeweizen, we infused a decadent dose of blood orange, resulting a supremely satisfying and refreshing beer with a hue that reminds you of that sunrise after you got away with something glorious!

name: Bowman Brown Ale
description: A robust american brown ale featuring Columbus, Chinook and Willamette hops.  Generous amounts of british crystal and chocolate malts import notes of caramel, toffee and chocolate. A crushable, smooth and dark yet dry ale, a notch below a porter

name: Cranberry, Peach, Passionfruit & Hibiscus Kettle Sour
Dark Bent
description: This dark stout done in the style of the world's most popular stout will not let you down. Rich in flaver yet dry and drinkable, It's our love letter to fans of dark, malty beers with notes of chocolate,  coffee and light roasted malt flavors. If you've got a thing for the dark side you'll love Dark Bent.
